{"abstract":[{"text":"Frees the data in the array and resets the size to zero, while","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the underlying array is preserved for use elsewhere and returned"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the caller."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/ptrarray\/steal(len:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PtrArray","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PtrArray\/PtrArrayProtocol-Implementations"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"steal"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"len"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"gsize","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gsize"},{"kind":"text","text":">! = nil) -> "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Sp","text":"UnsafeMutablePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@gpointer","text":"gpointer","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":"?>!","kind":"text"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that if the array is "},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" terminated this may still return"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"NULL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" if the length of the array was zero and pdata was not yet"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"allocated.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even if set, the [callback"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/DestroyNotify"},{"text":"] function will never be called","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"on the current contents of the array and the caller is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"responsible for freeing the array elements.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"An example of use:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["`g_autoptr(GPtrArray)` chunk_buffer = g_ptr_array_new_with_free_func (g_bytes_unref);","","\/\/ Some part of your application appends a number of chunks to the pointer array.","g_ptr_array_add (chunk_buffer, g_bytes_new_static (\"hello\", 5));","g_ptr_array_add (chunk_buffer, g_bytes_new_static (\"world\", 5));","","…","","\/\/ Periodically, the chunks need to be sent as an array-and-length to some","\/\/ other part of the program.","GBytes **chunks;","gsize n_chunks;","","chunks = g_ptr_array_steal (chunk_buffer, &n_chunks);","for (gsize i = 0; i < n_chunks; i++)","  {","    \/\/ Do something with each chunk here, and then free them, since","    \/\/ `g_ptr_array_steal()` transfers ownership of all the elements and the","    \/\/ array to the caller.","    …","","    g_bytes_unref (chunks[i]);","  }","","g_free (chunks);","","\/\/ After calling `g_ptr_array_steal()`, the pointer array can be reused for the","\/\/ next set of chunks.","g_assert (chunk_buffer->len == 0);"],"syntax":"c"}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PtrArray\/steal(len:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:4GLib16PtrArrayProtocolPAAE5steal3lenSpySvSgGSgSpySuGSg_tF::SYNTHESIZED::s:4GLib8PtrArrayC","roleHeading":"Instance Method","extendedModule":"GLib","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"steal","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"text":"len","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIde